# Basic to Advanced Python Projects

A collection of Python programs covering fundamental to advanced 
programming concepts, built progressively over time.

---

## Topics Covered

- **Basics** — Variables, data types, operators, input/output
- **Control Flow** — Conditionals, loops, nested logic
- **Functions** — Parameters, return values, recursion
- **Object Oriented Programming** — Classes, objects, inheritance,
  polymorphism, encapsulation
- **Data Structures** — Lists, tuples, dictionaries, sets
- **File Handling** — Reading and writing files
- **Modules** — Custom modules, imports
- **Advanced Projects** — ATM system, student management,
  GSM simulation, movie tasks

---

## Notable Projects

| Project | Description |
|---|---|
| `ATM_Code.py` | Simulated ATM system with transactions |
| `GSM.py` | GSM network simulation |
| `moviesTask.py` | Movie data management system |
| `Student.py` | Student record management using OOP |
| `MultipleInheritence.py` | Advanced OOP concepts |

---

## Language
```python
Python 3.x
```

---

## How to Run
1. Clone this repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/husnainalix77/Basic-to-Advanced-Python-Projects.git
```
2. Navigate to any file
```bash
cd Basic-to-Advanced-Python-Projects
python filename.py
```

